  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Capsule endoscopy has been shown to be the first-line endoscopic procedure for small bowel
      disease. This study was aimed to compare the performance between the frequency-altering AKE-1
      capsule and the Pillcam SB2 in patients with suspected small bowel disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
